    <note>Sun(1) Zairong [11790] See documentation for son, Xi [11791], and daughter-in-law, born Zhuang(1) Shi [11792]. The Sun were a multigenerational wealthy lineage (shi fuxing) of Yangzhou, Jiangdu (Guangling) county. When Zairong's younger brother married, he requested that the family divide their property in houses, fields, etc. Apparently, Zairong (who was neither eldest nor youngest) refused his portion of the inheritance and moved to Zhenzhou, Yangzi (modern Yizheng) county. His brothers went broke and in the end he was again head of a wealthy lineage (fuxing).</note>
